me in many of his documentaries is urban life.  His most notable documentaries include: Stations of the Elevated, We Were So Beloved, Tall: The American Skyscraper and Louis Sullivan, and Art Is... The Permanent Revolution.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T16:02:07.024085+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4595, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manfred_Kirchheimer"}], "uuid": "de956b2f-70d0-4bc2-80db-254be030c499", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "24250", "external_references": [{"id": 26660, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q17306150"}, {"id": 30068, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "5089872"}, {"id": 30069, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n97037126"}, {"id": 30070, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n97037126"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:31:08.174986+10:00"}]}